h expansion. He also addresses other interpretive problems in Eliot's mission, such as why the Puritans postponed their evangelizing mission until 1646, why Indians accepted or rejected the mission, and whether the mission played a role in causing King Philip's War. This book makes signal contributions to New England history, Native American history, and religious studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aIndians of North AmericaxMissionsxMassachusetts. 0aIndians of North AmericaxMissionsxNew EnglandxNeuenglandxIndianerxMassachusetts. 0aMissionariesxBiographyxMassachusetts. 0aMissionsxHistoryx17th centuryxMassachusetts. 0aPuritansxBiographyxMassachusetts. 0aPuritansxNew England. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z978311044221240uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674029637zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674029637423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674029637/original  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK